4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, a person and facility must
6 be licensed by the Alabama State Board of Prosthetists
7 and Orthotists to provide prosthetic, orthotic, or
8 pedorthic care in the state.
9 This bill would abolish the board and the
10 requirement to be licensed by the board to provide
11 prosthetic, orthotic, or pedorthic care.
12 This bill would require all individuals and
13 facilities providing prosthetic, orthotic, or pedorthic
14 care to be certified by a national certifying entity
15 approved by the Alabama Department of Workforce.
16 This bill would require certified persons to
17 submit proof of certification to the department to be
18 recorded by the department.
19 This bill would authorize the department to levy
20 an annual recording fee on certified persons to be
21 deposited into the State Treasury.
22 This bill would provide criminal penalties for
23 violations.
24
